1          /*------------------------------------------------------------------*
2          | PROGRAM NAME : SAStoCSVcli20260320.sas
3          | SHORT DESC   : Batch converts all SAS datasets in a directory to
4          |                CSV format via command-line interface
5          *------------------------------------------------------------------*
6          | CREATED BY   : DAC Development Team
7          | DATE CREATED : 2025-11-21
8          *------------------------------------------------------------------*
9          | PURPOSE
10         | Exports all SAS datasets (.sas7bdat) found in a specified input
11         | directory to CSV format. Output CSV files are placed in a
12         | DAC_CSV subfolder within the specified output directory. An error
13         | log file (error_log.txt) is written to the DAC_Logs subdirectory upon
14         | completion summarizing any SAS errors encountered.
15         |
16         | 1.0: REQUIRED SYSPARM PARAMETERS (pipe-delimited)
17         | INPUT_DIRECTORY  = Path to the folder containing .sas7bdat files
18         |                    to be converted
19         | OUTPUT_DIRECTORY = Path to the folder where the DAC_CSV subfolder
20         |                    and error log will be created
21         |
22         | 2.0: OPTIONAL PARAMETERS
23         | None. All parameters are supplied via SYSPARM.
24         |
25         | USAGE:
2                                           The SAS System                  14:16 Monday, July 6, 2026

26         |   sas -sysparm "input_directory|output_directory"
27         |       -sysin SAStoCSVcli20260320.sas
28         |
29         | OUTPUT STRUCTURE:
30         |   output_directory\
31         |   ├── DAC_CSV\              - CSV exports of all SAS datasets
32         |   └── DAC_Logs\
33         |       └── error_log.txt     - Error summary from the SAS run
34         *------------------------------------------------------------------*
35         | OPERATING SYSTEM COMPATIBILITY
36         | SAS v9.4 or Higher: Yes
37         *------------------------------------------------------------------*
38         | MACRO CALL
39         |
40         | Not applicable. Script is invoked directly via the SAS command
41         | line using -sysin and -sysparm.
42         *------------------------------------------------------------------*
43         | EXAMPLES
44         |
45         | Basic usage:
46         |   sas -sysparm "C:\data\input|C:\data\output"
47         |       -sysin SAStoCSVcli20260320.sas
48         |
49         | Using a study-specific output folder:
50         |   sas -sysparm "C:\studies\trial1\sas|C:\studies\trial1\output"
51         |       -sysin SAStoCSVcli20260320.sas
52         *------------------------------------------------------------------*/
